cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with visual supervised domain adaptation and generalization with deep models, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Siamese architecture and deep learning, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of probability distributions, which is a common topic in natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with visual domains, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
